                            <div class="gb-collapse">
                                <div itemscope="" itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question"
                                    class="gb-collapse__item ">
                                    <div class="gb-collapse__toggle"><a href="#" class="gb-collapse__link">
                                            <div itemprop="name"><i class="fa fa-angle-down"></i><span>What’s the
                                                    difference between Managed Hosting and Shared Hosting?</span></div>
                                        </a></div>
                                    <div class="ReactCollapse--collapse" style="height:0px;overflow:hidden"
                                        aria-hidden="true">
                                        <div class="ReactCollapse--content">
                                            <div itemscope="" itemprop="acceptedAnswer"
                                                itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="gb-collapse__content">
                                                <div itemprop="text">
                                                    <div>
                                                        <div class="gb-mb-2">Managed WordPress Hosting is a hosting
                                                            environment that is specifically designed for WordPress,
                                                            which doesn’t require any maintenance on your part. With
                                                            Shared Hosting, you share your resources with other website
                                                            owners. This means that if someone else’s website gets a lot
                                                            of traffic, you may experience downtime.</div>
                                                        <div>With Managed Hosting you’ll also never notice if a server
                                                            or any hardware fails because your website stays
                                                            containerised from such incidents.</div>
                                                    </div>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div itemscope="" itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question"
                                    class="gb-collapse__item ">
                                    <div class="gb-collapse__toggle"><a href="#" class="gb-collapse__link">
                                            <div itemprop="name"><i class="fa fa-angle-down"></i><span>Does EasyWP
                                                    include cPanel?</span></div>
                                        </a></div>
                                    <div class="ReactCollapse--collapse" style="height:0px;overflow:hidden"
                                        aria-hidden="true">
                                        <div class="ReactCollapse--content">
                                            <div itemscope="" itemprop="acceptedAnswer"
                                                itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="gb-collapse__content">
                                                <div itemprop="text">
                                                    <div>No, EasyWP doesn’t include cPanel. Instead we designed a
                                                        single, customized <a
                                                            href="https://www.namecheap.com/support/knowledgebase/article.aspx/9867/2239/easywp-dashboard-overview">dashboard</a>
                                                        to easily manage all your EasyWP websites—without any cPanel
                                                        hassle. All the tools you need to maintain and manage are
                                                        literally at your fingertips, whether that’s connecting a domain
                                                        name or managing your backups. With your EasyWP dashboard, it
                                                        only takes a few clicks. </div>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div itemscope="" itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question"
                                    class="gb-collapse__item ">
                                    <div class="gb-collapse__toggle"><a href="#" class="gb-collapse__link">
                                            <div itemprop="name"><i class="fa fa-angle-down"></i><span>Can I use any
                                                    domain name with EasyWP?</span></div>
                                        </a></div>
                                    <div class="ReactCollapse--collapse" style="height:0px;overflow:hidden"
                                        aria-hidden="true">
                                        <div class="ReactCollapse--content">
                                            <div itemscope="" itemprop="acceptedAnswer"
                                                itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="gb-collapse__content">
                                                <div itemprop="text">
                                                    <div>EasyWP works with any domain name, registered with any domain
                                                        provider. If your domain name is already registered with
                                                        Namecheap, it automatically connects to EasyWP. If your domain
                                                        name is registered elsewhere, we make it easy to connect it to
                                                        EasyWP. <a class="gb-text-bold gb-text-reset"
                                                            href="https://www.namecheap.com/support/knowledgebase/article.aspx/10029/2239">Learn
                                                            More</a></div>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div itemscope="" itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question"
                                    class="gb-collapse__item ">
                                    <div class="gb-collapse__toggle"><a href="#" class="gb-collapse__link">
                                            <div itemprop="name"><i class="fa fa-angle-down"></i><span>Can I use
                                                    custom themes and plugins with EasyWP?</span></div>
                                        </a></div>
                                    <div class="ReactCollapse--collapse" style="height:0px;overflow:hidden"
                                        aria-hidden="true">
                                        <div class="ReactCollapse--content">
                                            <div itemscope="" itemprop="acceptedAnswer"
                                                itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="gb-collapse__content">
                                                <div itemprop="text">
                                                    <div>Generally speaking, you can install any theme or plugin of your
                                                        choice using WordPress dashboard. We recommend you avoid
                                                        untrusted sources, as well as illegal free downloads of premium
                                                        themes and plugins. These can break your website and compromise
                                                        its security. We also have a <a
                                                            href="https://www.namecheap.com/support/knowledgebase/article.aspx/10015/2239/what-is-easywp-plugin#ewpblplgn">shortlist
                                                            of banned plugins</a> that are known to hurt your website or
                                                        cause performance issues.</div>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <p class="gb-mt-2"><span><a class="gb-text-bold"
                                        href="/support/knowledgebase/category/2239/easywp">View All →</a></span></p>
                        </div>
